The '''Senate Action Subcommittee for Corellian Trade Spine Defense''' was an [[Senate Action Subcommittee|action subcommittee]] of the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Galactic Senate]] formed during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] to coordinate the defense against [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederate]] encroachment along the [[Corellian Trade Spine/Legends|Corellian Trade Spine]]. It was chaired by [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Onaconda Farr/Legends|Onaconda Farr]].

In [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]], Farr used his position to transfer three newly commissioned [[Venator-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Venator''-class Star Destroyers]] from their assignment at [[Duro/Legends|Duro]] using fraudulent requisition datamemos placing the three vessels as undergoing "shakedown refurbishment" at a classified location. In reality, they had been transferred to [[Rodia/Legends|Rodia]]. He additionally bribed the [[Iseno/Legends|Iseno]] Senator [[Ronet Coorr]] to redistribute warships from Iseno to Rodia with millions of credits and promised rebuilding contracts on Ando. That year, [[Battle of Duro (Clone Wars)|Duro fell]] to the Confederacy, and an [[Senate Bureau of Intelligence/Legends|SBI]] report a month later revealed Farr's complacency in the event. He withdrew from his position in the Senate.

Later, critics of Republic policy used the corruption to advocate weakening or eliminating all action subcommittees.

